---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'africa-considerations', text: 'Africa-Specific Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'South Africa Insurance', href: '/insurance-for/expats' },
  { title: 'Evacuation Coverage Guide', href: '/guides/medical-evacuation-coverage' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Africa Network', cigna: 'Very Good', bupa: 'Good', allianz: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', cigna: 'Unlimited', bupa: 'Unlimited', allianz: '€1M - €3M' },
  { feature: 'South Africa', cigna: 'Excellent', bupa: 'Very Good', allianz: 'Very Good' },
  { feature: 'Kenya/Nigeria', cigna: 'Good', bupa: 'Good', allianz: 'Adequate' },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', cigna: 'Excellent', bupa: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Security Evacuation', cigna: 'Optional', bupa: 'Optional', allianz: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Direct Billing', cigna: 'Best', bupa: 'Good', allianz: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Best For', cigna: 'Overall choice', bupa: 'Premium service', allianz: 'Value option' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 35', cigna: '$280-450/mo', bupa: '$300-480/mo', allianz: '$200-320/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', cigna: '$400-600/mo', bupa: '$450-650/mo', allianz: '$300-450/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 40', cigna: '$650-950/mo', bupa: '$700-1,000/mo', allianz: '$480-720/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', cigna: '$900-1,400/mo', bupa: '$1,000-1,500/mo', allianz: '$700-1,050/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Best Insurance for Africa Expats 2026"
  description="Compare insurance for expats in Africa: Cigna Global, Bupa Global, and Allianz Care. Networks, evacuation coverage, and considerations for South Africa, Kenya, Nigeria, and beyond."
  headline="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Africa Expat Insurance Compared"
  subheadline="Africa requires robust coverage with strong evacuation benefits. Here's how the three major insurers compare for the continent."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Overall</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Best network in Africa. Strongest direct billing. Excellent evacuation coordination. The safe choice.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Premium Service</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Excellent evacuation. Good South Africa network. Lifetime renewal. Premium customer care.</p>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">20-30% cheaper. Solid evacuation coverage. Good for South Africa. More reimbursement needed.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Africa presents unique challenges: variable healthcare quality, potential need for evacuation, and fewer direct billing options. Cigna has the strongest Africa presence. Bupa offers premium service. Allianz provides value but with a smaller network.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Evacuation</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Direct Billing</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global is the strongest choice for Africa. They have the most extensive network, best direct billing relationships with private hospitals, and excellent evacuation coordination. Most corporate expats in Africa use Cigna for good reason.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Best provider network across Africa</li>
    <li>Strong direct billing at Netcare, Life Healthcare, Aga Khan</li>
    <li>Excellent medical evacuation coordination</li>
    <li>24/7 assistance with Africa expertise</li>
    <li>Unlimited coverage</li>
    <li>Security evacuation add-on available</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive option</li>
    <li>Network still limited in some countries</li>
    <li>Strict pre-existing condition handling</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Corporate expats. Anyone in remote or challenging locations. Those who want the best evacuation support. Expats who prioritize direct billing.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="bupa-global">Bupa Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Premium Service</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Strong Evacuation</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Lifetime Renewal</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium service with strong evacuation coverage. Their network is smaller than Cigna's in Africa, but they excel at coordinating complex care and evacuations. Lifetime renewal means they can't drop you if you develop conditions.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Excellent evacuation coordination</li>
    <li>Premium customer service</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
    <li>Good South Africa network</li>
    <li>Security evacuation available</li>
    <li>Strong claims support</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive option</li>
    <li>Smaller network outside South Africa</li>
    <li>More reimbursement claims needed</li>
    <li>App not as polished as Cigna</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Long-term Africa expats. Those who value lifetime renewal. Expats prioritizing service over network size. South Africa-based professionals.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good Evacuation</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Flexible Underwriting</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care offers solid Africa coverage at 20-30% less than competitors. The network is smaller, meaning more reimbursement claims, but evacuation coverage is good and they're more flexible on pre-existing conditions. Best value for cost-conscious expats.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>20-30% cheaper than Cigna/Bupa</li>
    <li>Good evacuation coverage</li>
    <li>More flexible on pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>Strong mental health benefits</li>
    <li>Good South Africa coverage</li>
    <li>Moratorium underwriting option</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Limited direct billing in Africa</li>
    <li>More reimbursement claims needed</li>
    <li>€3M limit (vs unlimited)</li>
    <li>Smaller assistance network</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Budget-conscious expats. Those in South Africa where network is strongest. Anyone with pre-existing conditions. Expats comfortable with reimbursement.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare All Three"
    description="Get personalized quotes for your Africa destination. Consider evacuation needs carefully."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    Africa coverage costs vary by country—South Africa is relatively affordable, while remote locations cost more due to evacuation risk. All prices assume comprehensive coverage with evacuation.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for Africa coverage including evacuation. Prices vary significantly by specific country, age, and health status.
  </p>

  <h2 id="africa-considerations">Africa-Specific Considerations</h2>

  <h3>Medical Evacuation Is Critical</h3>
  <p>
    Africa has excellent healthcare in major cities (Johannesburg, Nairobi, Lagos) but limited facilities elsewhere. Medical evacuation coverage is essential—a medevac can cost $50,000-200,000 out of pocket. All three insurers include evacuation, but quality varies:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Best evacuation coordination, own assistance network</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Excellent evacuation support, strong partnerships</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Good evacuation, may take longer to coordinate</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Security Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    Some African countries have security risks. Security/political evacuation is typically an add-on:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Covers evacuation due to war, civil unrest, terrorism</li>
    <li>Cost: typically $100-300/year extra</li>
    <li>Essential for high-risk countries</li>
    <li>Check if your employer provides separate coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Country-Specific Networks</h3>

  <h4>South Africa</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Excellent—Netcare, Life Healthcare, Mediclinic</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Very good—major private hospital groups</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Good coverage in major cities</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Kenya</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Good—Aga Khan, Nairobi Hospital</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Good coverage in Nairobi</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Limited direct billing</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Nigeria</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Good—St. Nicholas, Reddington</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Adequate in Lagos</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Limited coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Other Countries</h4>
  <p>
    For countries like Ghana, Tanzania, Ethiopia, or remote locations: expect more reimbursement claims and plan for potential evacuation to South Africa or home country for serious care.
  </p>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want the best network in Africa</li>
        <li>Need strong evacuation support</li>
        <li>Prefer direct billing over reimbursement</li>
        <li>Are in a remote or challenging location</li>
        <li>Work for a corporation</li>
        <li>Value the best digital experience</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Plan to stay in Africa long-term</li>
        <li>Want lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
        <li>Value premium customer service</li>
        <li>Are primarily in South Africa</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Want strong evacuation coordination</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are budget-conscious</li>
        <li>Are primarily in South Africa</li>
        <li>Are comfortable with reimbursement claims</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions to cover</li>
        <li>Want good mental health coverage</li>
        <li>€3M coverage limit is sufficient</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is international insurance necessary in South Africa?</h3>
  <p>
    South Africa has excellent private healthcare, but it's expensive. International insurance gives you access to the best private hospitals and provides evacuation if needed for specialized care not available locally.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I need emergency care in a remote area?</h3>
  <p>
    Call your insurer's 24/7 assistance line immediately. They'll coordinate local care and evacuation if needed. All three insurers have experience with African evacuations—Cigna and Bupa have slight edges in coordination speed.
  </p>

  <h3>Should I add security evacuation coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    Depends on your location. For stable countries (South Africa, Kenya, Ghana), it's optional. For higher-risk countries or remote areas, strongly recommended. Cost is typically $100-300/year—cheap insurance for political instability.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use local African insurance instead?</h3>
  <p>
    South Africa has good local options (Discovery Health, Momentum). But local insurance typically doesn't cover evacuation outside the country or care when traveling. International insurance is more flexible.
  </p>

  <h3>Which insurer is best for NGO/humanitarian workers?</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna has the most experience with humanitarian organizations. However, specialized providers like GeoBlue or Aetna may offer group plans designed for NGO work. Ask about crisis support and security evacuation.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Africa coverage needs vary dramatically by country. Verify evacuation terms and country-specific network coverage directly with each insurer before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
